This paper is about a technique for identifying refactorings in software systems, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of static analysis and code similarity, which are topics that fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents an evaluation of the approach, which involves metrics and statistical analysis, topics that fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
